<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Longshots Win at Aqueduct </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Charge d'Affaires, an 11-1 shot, rallied for a  
head victory over Comic Strip in the $110,80 Knickerbocker Handicap 
at Aqueduct Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	The 4-year-old colt, recently recovered from foot problems,  
showed his top form while carrying 114 pounds with Jose Santos over 
1 1/8 miles on the turf course in 1:49. He earned $66,480 for the 
Marquise de Mortalla. 
</P>
<P>
	Comic Strip closed well to be second in the field of seven, a  
length ahead of Nat's Big Party. 
</P>
<P>
	The winner returned $25, $6.60 and $3.20, Comic Strip paid $2.50  
and $2.10 and Nat's Big Party was $2.70 to show. 
</P>
<P>
	Belle Cherie, a 6-1 shot ridden by John Velazquez, won the  
co-featured $110,000 Turnback the Alarm Handicap by three lengths. 
Velazquez also was aboard Snit, the winner of last year's race. 
</P>
<P>
	Belle Cherie carried 112 pounds over 1 1/8 miles in 1:50 and earned  
$66,000 for Bellemeadows Farm and Lael Stable. It was the second 
win in six starts this year for the 3-year-old filly. 
</P>
<P>
	Brushed Halory was runner-up in the field of eight, 1 1/4 lengths  
ahead of Sweet Misty. 
</P>
<P>
	Belle Cherie returned $14.60, $8.20 and $7.90. Brushed Halory  
paid $7.90 and $6.20 and Sweet Misty was $10.20 to show. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
