<DOCNO> APW19991030.0010 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-30 08:40:04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Kawagishi Leads Japan Golf by One  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	KATO, Japan (AP) -- Ryoken Kawagishi made four consecutive birdie  
putts in a bogey-free round of 6-under-par 66 Saturday that gave 
him a one-stroke lead after 54 holes of the $1.9 million Philip 
Morris Championship. 
</P>
<P>
	Kawagishi, pursuing his first victory on the Japanese tour since  
1995, birdied the second hole then began a rampage on the par-5 
fourth at the 7,176-yard ABC Golf Club. He finished the third round 
14 under at 202. 
</P>
<P>
	One shot behind Kawagishi entering the final 18 holes Sunday is  
second-round leader Katsunori Kuwabara, who had a 69 Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Kaname Yokoo and Myanmar's Zaw Moe were at 205. Yokoo had a 67  
Saturday, and Moe carded a 71. 
</P>
<P>
	Naomichi ``Joe'' Ozaki, seeking his fourth win this year, had a  
67, and was tied with four others six shots off the lead in the 
chase for a winning purse of $381,388. 
</P>
</TEXT>
