<HEADLINE> Former Twins Owner Griffith Buried </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BRENTWOOD, Md. (AP) -- Former Minnesota Twins owner Calvin  
Griffith, who spent more than 60 years in the organization, was 
buried Saturday in this Washington suburb. 
</P>
<P>
	In the 1920s, Griffith was a bat boy and mascot for the  
Washington Senators and later managed in the minor league system 
and worked in the front office. He took over the team in 1955, when 
his father died. He moved the Senators to Minnesota after the 1960 
season, angering fans. 
</P>
<P>
	Griffith, who died Oct. 20 in Melbourne, Fla., at 87, sold the  
Twins in 1984. 
</P>
<P>
	The funeral at the Fort Lincoln Cemetery and Funeral Home  
followed a memorial service Thursday in Minneapolis. 
  	   	
</P>
