<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Moments of Magic Wins Dowager Stakes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LEXINGTON, Ky. (AP) -- Favored Moments of Magic caught Kris Is It  
at the top of the stretch and then held off Queen's Legend to win 
the $113,100 Dowager Stakes as Keeneland ended its fall meeting 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	The 4-year-old filly by Danzig was kept close to the leaders  
throughout the 1 1/2-mile race by jockey Shane Sellers, and ran the 
distance on the firm turf course in a stakes record 2:29 4-5. The 
previous record was 2:31. 
</P>
<P>
	Moments of Magic finished 2 1/2 lengths in front of Queen's Legend.  
It was 1 1/2 lengths back to third-place Penne in the field of nine 
fillies and mares. 
</P>
<P>
	It was the fourth win in 14 career starts for Moments of Magic,  
who increased her lifetime earnings to $218,392 for owners G. Watts 
Humphrey Jr. and Louise I. Humphrey. 
</P>
<P>
	The winner paid $4, $2.80 and $2.60. Queen's Legend, who charged  
from behind under Larry Melancon to contend for the lead at the top 
of the stretch, returned $5.80 and $4. Penne returned $9.40 to 
show. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
