<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-30 13:50:16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Blazers' Musselman in Hospital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PORTLAND, Ore. (AP) -- Assistant coach Bill Musselman of the  
Portland Trail Blazers was in serious condition Saturday following 
a possible stroke. 
</P>
<P>
	``He is in stable condition and we're just waiting to see,''  
said Phyllis Riggs, a nursing supervisor at Legacy Emanuel 
Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
	Musselman, 59, collapsed after Thursday night's exhibition game  
against Phoenix, Leonard Greene, a team spokesman, said. Musselman 
wasn't in the arena when he collapsed, Greene said. 
</P>
<P>
	Musselman, who joined the Blazers in 1997, took over the head  
coaching job for the game after Mike Dunleavy was ejected. 
</P>
<P>
	His previous NBA experience included head coaching jobs with  
Cleveland and Minnesota. 
</P>
<P>
	He then coached at South Alabama, leading the Jaguars to a 27-12  
record, a Sun Belt Conference co-title and an NCAA tournament 
berth. He also has coached at Ashland and the University of 
Minnesota. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
