<CATEGORY> washington </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Clinton, Senators at Chafee Funeral </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PROVIDENCE, R.I. (AP) -- President Clinton, about half the U.S.  
Senate and a host of other dignitaries arrived in Rhode Island 
today for the funeral of deceased U.S. Sen. John H. Chafee. 
</P>
<P>
	The turnout of national figures was among the largest ever for  
the funeral of a U.S. senator -- a reflection of the admiration the 
moderate Republican earned during his four decades of public 
service, including 23 years in the Senate. Chafee died Sunday of 
heart failure at age 77. 
</P>
<P>
	Chafee's flag-draped coffin was removed today from the Rhode  
Island State House, where the late senator lay in state since 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	Six Marine Corps pallbears then placed the coffin onto a  
carriage, and two horses pulled the carriage through downtown 
streets lined with people paying their last respects 
</P>
<P>
	Following the carriage on foot were Chafee's five adult  
children, including Warwick Mayor Lincoln Chafee, who is running 
for his late father's seat in the U.S. Senate. 
</P>
<P>
	Eight black limousines completed the procession, carrying  
Chafee's wife, Virginia, and her grandchildren. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
