<HEADLINE> British Comedy Honored in Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Valladolid, Spain (AP) -- ``East is East,'' a comedy about a  
mixed-race family in northern England directed by newcomer Damien 
O'Donnell, was awarded the Golden Ear of Corn for best picture at 
the Valladolid Film Festival in Spain on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Tim Roth won the second-place Silver Ear of Corn for his far  
darker journey into family life and incest in ``The War Zone,'' the 
actor's debut as a director. 
</P>
<P>
	Linda Basset, who plays the Caucasian wife of a Pakistani  
shopkeeper in ``East is East,'' was named as best actress by the 
jury of the international film festival, held yearly in this 
north-central Spanish city. 
</P>
<P>
	Japanese actor/director Beat Takeshi was named best actor for  
his role in his own film ``Kikujiro,'' a humorous journey of 
self-discovery marking a departure from the gangster focus of his 
previous movies. 
  	   	
</P>
