<CATEGORY> international </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Fire at S.Korea Store Kills 57 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
                          *By SANG-HUN CHOE    	
</P>
<P>
                      *Associated Press Writer    	
</P>
<P>
	SEOUL, South Korea (AP) -- A fire raged through a four-story  
building crowded with young weekend shoppers and diners today in 
northwestern South Korea, killing at least 57 people, many of them 
teen-agers, police said. It was the worst fire in 25 years. 
</P>
<P>
	Seventy people were injured, some of them seriously. Police said  
the death toll may rise further because some of the injured people 
were in critical condition. 
</P>
<P>
	The fire broke out around 7 p.m. in Inchon, South Korea's third  
largest city, 30 miles west of Seoul. The blaze gutted the building 
packed with restaurants, karaoke clubs, a beer bar and billiard 
room. 
</P>
<P>
	Most of the victims were teen-agers or in their early 20s,  
police said. The building was located in the city's central 
commercial district, which was bustling with young people on the 
weekend. 
</P>
<P>
	Fire engines rushed to the scene and extinguished the fire in 40  
minutes, police said. The cause of the fire was still unknown. 
</P>
<P>
	Most of the dead were found in a second-floor beer bar and  
third-floor billiard room, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	``The fire spread so quickly that by the time we got into the  
beer bar, we found many people already dead. They appeared to have 
suffocated from the smoke,'' said local police chief Park 
Myong-hwan. ``Many of the bodies were found clustered near the 
bar's main door.'' 
</P>
<P>
	TV footage showed firefighters picking through the scorched  
stores and restaurants. Police carried injured people to ambulances 
and raced to nearby hospitals. 
</P>
<P>
	``There were so many people carried out of the building, but  
there were not enough ambulances and so firefighters left them on 
the pavement and rushed back inside to get more people out,'' 
witness Woo Sung-hwan, 43, told the national news agency Yonhap. 
</P>
<P>
	The fire is the worst since a hotel fire killed 88 people in  
Seoul in 1974. Three years before that, another hotel fired killed 
165 people in Seoul. 
</P>
<P>
	KBS television said the fire appeared to have broken out in an  
underground karaoke shop. 
</P>
<P>
	Workers were renovating the shop and were using paint thinners,  
reports said. 
</P>
<P>
	``I heard a blast and then saw smoke filling up the building and  
people scrambling out,'' said another witness, Park Hyun-sok, told 
the all news cable channel, YTN. 
</P>
<P>
	The flames raced quickly upward, burning plastic furniture and  
carpets, the reports said. Toxic smoke quickly filled the building, 
which lacked big windows. The smoke trapped people in upper floors 
because it moved up the stairs, they said. 
</P>
<P>
	Meanwhile, dozens of family members were wailing and praying  
outside the intensive care unit of the city's Inha University 
Hospital, where many victims were hospitalized, according to TV 
footage. 
</P>
<P>
	Running short of beds, doctors and nurses laid some of the  
bodies on the floor covered with white sheets, the footage showed. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
