<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-30 11:40:04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Brewers Reportedly Mulling Lopes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MILWAUKEE (AP) -- San Diego Padres first base coach Davey Lopes  
is a leading contender to be the Milwaukee Brewers' new manager, 
the Milwaukee Journal Sentinel reported Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Lopes has been invited Monday for a second interview with the  
Brewers, the newspaper said. The interview would include club 
president Wendy Selig-Prieb, who did not participate in the initial 
interview. 
</P>
<P>
	The Brewers declined comment on whether Lopes has been asked  
back. The newspaper based its report on an unidentified source 
``familiar with the search process.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The Brewers, who might announce their choice for a new manager  
as early as next week, also could bring back New York Yankees third 
base coach Willie Randolph for another interview, the newspaper 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	Lopes has been San Diego's first base coach for five seasons.  
Before that, he spent four years as a dugout coach and first base 
coach with the Texas Rangers, and served for three years as a first 
base coach with the Baltimore Orioles. 
</P>
<P>
	Yankees batting coach Chris Chambliss has also interviewed with  
the Brewers. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
