</P>
<P>
	-- the IOC to have a maximum of 115 members.  
</P>
<P>
	-- 15 active athletes to be appointed as full IOC members.  
</P>
<P>
	-- the renovated IOC to include 15 presidents of international  
federations and 15 presidents of national Olympic committees or 
continental associations. 
</P>
<P>
	-- 70 members to be elected on an individual basis.  
</P>
<P>
	-- creation of a special selection committee to screen candidates  
for IOC membership. 
</P>
<P>
	-- the executive board to be expanded from 11 members to 15, with  
a permanent seat reserved for athletes. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
