<HEADLINE> Overzealous Security Guard Sentenced </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MIAMI (AP) -- An overzealous security guard intent on protecting  
parking spots for bank customers was sentenced to 20 years for 
killing a driver delivering frozen chickens next door. 
</P>
<P>
	Carlos Valdes, 69, and relatives asked for leniency, but Circuit  
Judge Marc Schumacher imposed what may amount to a life term for a 
man with a heart condition because Valdes failed to take full 
responsibility. 
</P>
<P>
	Even at sentencing Friday, Valdes faulted the unarmed victim,  
Abraham Oliden, 35, as the aggressor. 
</P>
<P>
	The two men argued in January 1998 when Oliden, who was  
delivering chickens to a restaurant next door, drove into the 
suburban bank lot and double parked. 
</P>
<P>
	Two gunshots hit the Peruvian immigrant in the chest and  
stomach, and he died in the arms of a witness. Valdes called 911. 
</P>
<P>
	Valdes claimed he acted in self-defense when Oliden reached  
toward his truck as if looking for a weapon. The only item police 
found inside was a cellular phone. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
