<HEADLINE> Red Sox Pick Up Cormier's Option </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- The Boston Red Sox picked up a $2 million option  
Saturday on left-handed reliever Rheal Cormier. 
</P>
<P>
	Cormier earned $950,000 last season, when he appeared in 60  
games and posted a 2-0 record and 3.69 ERA in the regular season. 
In the playoffs, he pitched 7 2-3 innings over six games and did 
not allow an earned run. 
</P>
<P>
	The Red Sox must decide by Monday whether to exercise a $3  
million option on pitcher Pat Rapp or give him a $250,00 buyout. 
Rapp was 6-7 with a 4.12 ERA in the regular season and pitched one 
scoreless inning in the playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
	A Red Sox spokesman said the team was waiting to hear whether  
Kent Mercker would exercise his $1.75 million option to return for 
next season. He must decide by Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Mercker went 2-0 with a 3.51 ERA after joining the Red Sox in  
midseason and went 0-1 with a 5.79 ERA in three playoff starts. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
