<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Fugitive DEA Agent Commits Suicide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- A fugitive DEA agent wanted in the deadly  
shooting of his estranged girlfriend shot and killed himself in 
Louisiana Saturday during a police pursuit. 
</P>
<P>
	Tony Gerard Bailey, 35, had been the subject of a nationwide  
manhunt since Wednesday night, when he barged into the Fullerton 
home where his estranged girlfriend was staying, shooting and 
killing her and wounding her sister. 
</P>
<P>
	Veda Harris, 32, with whom Bailey has a 2-year-old daughter, was  
pronounced dead at the scene. Her 36-year-old sister, Wendy 
Campbell, was shot in the stomach. She was hospitalized at 
University of California, Irvine, Medical Center. A message left 
Saturday for her condition wasn't returned. 
</P>
<P>
	Fullerton and Louisiana police officers said after Wednesday's  
shooting, Bailey fled in a sport utility vehicle. He was still 
driving it Saturday in Opelousas, La., when police spotted him in 
the neighborhood of his ex-brother-in-law. 
</P>
<P>
	About 2 p.m. CDT, Opelousas officers saw Bailey in his Ford  
Explorer. They ordered him to surrender, but he ran off. Officers 
chased after him. 
</P>
<P>
	``Bailey was armed with 9 mm semiautomatic,'' said Opelousas  
police Capt. Ronnie Trahan. ``He placed the gun to his head and 
fired.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Bailey was pronounced dead at the scene.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
