<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Mummified Body of Baby Found </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HUGO, Colo. (AP) -- Authorities were investigating the death of a  
baby boy whose mummified body was found in a cardboard box inside 
an old shed. 
</P>
<P>
	Authorities believe the baby was born in 1964 since a newspaper  
from that year was found with the body. 
</P>
<P>
	The baby was dressed in a night shirt and diaper and his  
umbilical cord had been tied off. He was wrapped in a pink baby 
blanket and there was a blue blanket under the body. 
</P>
<P>
	``It looks like there was some feeling for this child,'' said  
Arapahoe County coroner Mike Dobersen, who performed an autopsy 
Friday. Authorities said the baby may have been stillborn and that 
there was no indication of foul play. 
</P>
<P>
	The body was found Thursday when the owners of the property were  
cleaning out the shed. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
