<CATEGORY> international </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Israelis Hurt in West Bank Shooting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	JERUSALEM (AP) -- Five Israelis were injured Saturday when their  
bus was fired on in the West Bank, apparently by Palestinian 
assailants, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	The shooting attack came one day before Israeli, Palestinian and  
American leaders were to gather in Oslo for a summit to open final 
status talks on the most thorny issues of the peace process. 
</P>
<P>
	The bus was traveling from the settlement of Kiryat Arba when it  
was fired on near the Palestinian village of Tarkumiya, police 
spokesman Rafi Yaffe said. Five Israelis were slightly to 
moderately wounded, he added. 
</P>
<P>
	The area of the shooting is controlled by Israel, Israel radio  
reported. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
